discovery_rule.name: icmpMsgStatsEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: A conceptual row in the icmpMsgStatsTable. The system should track each ICMP type value, even if that ICMP type is not supported by the system. However, a given row need not be instantiated unless a message of that type has been processed, i.e., the row for icmpMsgStatsType=X MAY be instantiated before but MUST be instantiated after the first message with Type=X is received or transmitted. After receiving or transmitting any succeeding messages with Type=X, the relevant counter must be incremented.

item_prototype.name: icmpMsgStatsOutPkts for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of output packets for this AF and type.

item_prototype.name: icmpMsgStatsInPkts for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of input packets for this AF and type.

discovery_rule.name: icmpStatsEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: A conceptual row in the icmpStatsTable.

item_prototype.name: icmpStatsOutErrors for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of ICMP messages that this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP, such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer, such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations, there may be no types of error that contribute to this counter's value.

item_prototype.name: icmpStatsOutMsgs for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number of ICMP messages that the entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpStatsOutErrors.

item_prototype.name: icmpStatsInErrors for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The number of ICMP messages that the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

item_prototype.name: icmpStatsInMsgs for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: The total number of ICMP messages that the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpStatsInErrors.
